Sweet Movie is a 1974 avant-garde art house comedy-drama film by the Yugoslavian director Dusan Makavejev. 
The film is based on two narratives. One narrative follows Miss Monde 1984/Miss Canada (Carole Laure), who wins a contest of the "most virgin"; her prize is the marriage to a milk industry tycoon (John Vernon). However, following his degrading puritanical introduction to intercourse, she vents her intention to leave to her mother-in-law who, at that point, nearly has her killed. 
The second narrative involves a woman, Anna Planeta (Anna Prucnal) piloting a candy-filled boat in the canals of Amsterdam, the Netherlands, with a large papier-mache head of Karl Marx on the prow. She picks up the hitchhiking sailor Potemkin (Pierre ClÃ©menti), though she warns him that if he falls in love, she will kill him.
